12-//   structural cbuffer wrap of c-register-bound globals -- see the
13://   Rule D block below for full rationale). Whatever buffer Rule D
14-//   produces (or the original if no section was found) then feeds the
15://   single-pass A/B/C/E scanner. The main-source path skips Rule D
16-//   because main `.vsh` sources don't carry c-register globals.
17-//
18-//   Single-pass scanner walks the source byte-by-byte. At each position
19-//   it tries (in order):
20-//     1. Rule A: SM4+ reserved-keyword whole-word match (Iter-4 origin).
21-//        On match -- emit the keyword followed by the `_id` suffix; output
