Read-only trace complete. The strongest divergence is not where world/view/proj are cached; those are mostly mirrored. It is at the D3D11 CPU-to-shader boundary: D3D11 composes `P*V*W`, then transposes WVP and World before upload, while D3D9 VSPS uploads the `P*V*W` and World matrices untransposed to c0..c7.

**Side-By-Side Trace**

| Step | D3D9 `gl05` | D3D11 `gl11` |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Skeletal draw sets object transform | `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive::prepareToDraw()` gets `m_appearance.getTransform_w()` and calls `Graphics::setObjectToWorldTransformAndScale(transform_apw, Vector::xyz111)` at `src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:483-491`; `Graphics` dispatches plugin API at `clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:1486-1489`. | Same engine call path; plugin API wired to `Direct3d11_StateCache::setObjectToWorldTransformAndScale` at `Direct3d11.cpp:1057-1060`. |
| Object-to-world storage | Handler is `Direct3d9Namespace::setObjectToWorldTransformAndScale` at `Direct3d9.cpp:3402`; marks `ms_transformDirty`, calls `convertScaleAndTransformToMatrix(scale, transform, ms_cachedObjectToWorldMatrix)` at `Direct3d9.cpp:3409-3410`. VSPS conversion rows are `transform.matrix[0][0..3] * scale.x`, row 1 by `scale.y`, row 2 by `scale.z` at `Direct3d9.cpp:3155-3168`; row 4 was initialized once to `[0,0,0,1]` at `Direct3d9.cpp:1691-1701`. | Handler is `Direct3d11_StateCache::setObjectToWorldTransformAndScale` at `Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:1909`; caches raw transform for lighting, then builds `s_cachedWorld` with the same row-scaling shape at `Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:1942-1949`, then calls `composeSlot0Shadow()` at `:1951`. |
| View/camera storage | `setWorldToCameraTransform` at `Direct3d9.cpp:3271`; `convertTransformToMatrix(transform, ms_cachedWorldToCameraMatrix)` at `:3280`; VSPS conversion copies transform rows at `Direct3d9.cpp:3108-3121`, row 4 initialized once at `:1698-1701`; camera position goes to `VSCR_cameraPosition` at `:3288-3291`. | `Direct3d11_StateCache::setWorldToCameraTransform` at `Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:1789`; copies `objectToWorld.getMatrix()` rows into `s_cachedView` at `:1799-1805`, caches camera position, then recomposes slot shadow at `:1843-1844`. Parameter name is misleading, but storage shape matches D3D9’s VSPS view conversion. |
| Projection storage | `setProjectionMatrix` at `Direct3d9.cpp:3301`; VSPS branch copies `projectionMatrix.matrix[row][col]` directly into `ms_cachedProjectionMatrix` at `:3330-3348`. | `Direct3d11_StateCache::setProjectionMatrix` at `Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:1849`; `memcpy(&s_cachedProj, projectionMatrix.matrix, 16 floats)` at `:1859`, then recomposes at `:1861-1863`. Same layout as D3D9 VSPS. |
| View/projection composition | In VSPS, `ms_cachedWorldToProjectionMatrix = ms_cachedProjectionMatrix * ms_cachedWorldToCameraMatrix` at `Direct3d9.cpp:3291` and again after projection changes at `:3359`. | `composeSlot0Shadow()` loads `V/P/W` at `Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:331-333`; computes `wtp = XMMatrixMultiply(P, V)` and `wvp = XMMatrixMultiply(wtp, W)` at `:334-335`. Same intended symbolic order as D3D9 VSPS: `(P*V)*W`. |
| Final WVP upload | Draw path checks `ms_transformDirty`; VSPS branch does `D3DXMatrixMultiply(matrices+0, &ms_cachedWorldToProjectionMatrix, &ms_cachedObjectToWorldMatrix)` and `matrices[1] = ms_cachedObjectToWorldMatrix` at `Direct3d9.cpp:4026-4038`. Upload is raw `SetVertexShaderConstantF(index, data, count)` via `Direct3d9_StateCache.cpp:522-527`, with WVP at c0 and World at c4 per `Direct3d9_VertexShaderConstantRegisters.h:20-24`. | `composeSlot0Shadow()` transposes both `wvp` and `W` at `Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:352-355`, stores them into `s_slot0Shadow.objectWorldCameraProjectionMatrix` and `.objectWorldMatrix`, then lazy flush uploads full slot 0 with `Direct3d11_ConstantBuffer::updateVS(0, &s_slot0Shadow, sizeof(...))` at `:731`. `updateVS` maps/write-discard/memcpy/unmaps at `Direct3d11_ConstantBuffer.cpp:165-189`; slot b0 is bound by `bindVS(0)` at `Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:1353` and `VSSetConstantBuffers` at `Direct3d11_ConstantBuffer.cpp:221-228`. |
| Shader expectation | Legacy include uses `transform3d()` as `return mul(vertexPosition_o, objectWorldCameraProjectionMatrix);` in `stage/shader-rewrite-inc-1-input.txt:10-12`. | D3D11 wraps constants into `cbuffer SwgVertexConstants : register(b0)` with WVP at `packoffset(c0)` in `stage/shader-iter13b-inc-0-output.txt:95-98`; vertex compile explicitly sets `D3DCOMPILE_PACK_MATRIX_ROW_MAJOR` at `Direct3d11_VertexShaderData.cpp:907-920`. |

**Ranked Divergences**

1. **Highest likelihood: D3D11 transposes WVP/World before upload; D3D9 VSPS does not.**  
   D3D9 uploads `P*V*W` raw to c0..c3. D3D11 computes the same symbolic matrix, then stores `transpose(P*V*W)` at `Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:352-355`. Given the shader source uses row-vector `mul(vertexPosition_o, objectWorldCameraProjectionMatrix)` and D3D11 compiles row-major, this can move the camera-distance contribution out of clip W. That directly matches “object-local vertex maps to W ~= 0 / negative.”

2. **Medium likelihood: D3D11 recomposes and marks slot 0 dirty in every matrix setter, then flushes lazily before draw; D3D9 composes only in draw dispatch when `ms_transformDirty` is true.**  
   For `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive`, `prepareToDraw()` does call the object setter immediately before draw, so this is less likely than the transpose issue. But the timing is still structurally different: D3D11 flushes in `applyPreDrawState()` at `Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:1198`, while D3D9 uploads inside the draw path at `Direct3d9.cpp:4026-4038`.

3. **Low likelihood: D3D11 cbuffer packing/binding model differs from D3D9 register-file upload.**  
   D3D9 writes c0..c7 directly. D3D11 writes a 1152-byte b0 cbuffer with WVP at offset 0 and World at 64, with static asserts at `Direct3d11_ConstantBuffer.h:213-234`. The binding path looks coherent, so this is only a candidate if reflection/cache shows the active skeletal VS is not reading b0/c0 as expected.

4. **Low likelihood: world/view/projection source matrices differ.**  
   Object, view, and projection storage all match D3D9 VSPS layout closely: D3D9 object rows at `Direct3d9.cpp:3155-3168` vs D3D11 `s_cachedWorld` at `Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:1945-1949`; D3D9 projection rows at `Direct3d9.cpp:3330-3348` vs D3D11 memcpy at `Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:1859`.

No fixes made.
